xplicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"wordpress autoblogging plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=236477\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:619:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress autoblogging plugins? Starting a blog is easy but a lot of people struggle with producing content on a regular basis for their blog. WordPress autoblogging plugins allow you to curate content from other sources and display them on your blog. You can also rephrase and post fresh articles. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-autoblogging-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress Autoblogging Plugins to Autopilot Your Blog</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11187:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress autoblogging plugins? Starting a blog is easy but a lot of people struggle with producing content on a regular basis for their blog. </p>\n<p>WordPress autoblogging plugins allow you to curate content from other sources and display them on your blog. You can also rephrase and post fresh articles.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll share some of the best WordPress autoblogging plugins to autopilot your blog.</p>\n<h3>Why WordPress Autoblogging Plugins?</h3>\n<p>Running a blog and adding new content every day isn&#8217;t an easy job. With a WordPress autoblogging plugin, you can autopilot your blog and post new content on a regular basis. </p>\n<p>A WordPress autoblogging plugin imports content from various RSS feeds to your WordPress site. Some plugins even rephrase your WordPress content and ensures you have no duplicate content. </p>\n<p>There&#8217;re hundreds of free and premium WordPress plugins for autoblogging. But before you dive in and choose a plugin for your blog, keep in mind that autoblogging isn&#8217;t for everyone. While an autoblogging plugin makes it easy to post regular articles on your blog, instead of simply copying articles, it&#8217;s in your best interest to change your curated content in some way so as to ensure your site doesn&#8217;t get penalized for duplicate content. </p>\n<p>Here are a few recommended practices to follow if you&#8217;re using an autoblogging plugin.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Feature only excerpts instead of an entire article.</li>\n<li>Add twice as much original content than sourced content. </li>\n<li>Add commentary in between your gathered content.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/themeisle-freedzy-rss-feeds/\" title=\"Feedzy RSS\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">1. Feedzy RSS</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/themeisle-freedzy-rss-feeds/\" title=\"Feedzy RSS\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/feedzyrss.jpg\" alt=\"Feedzy RSS\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236482\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/feedzyrss.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/feedzyrss-300x97.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/feedzyrss-768x248.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/themeisle-freedzy-rss-feeds/\" title=\"Feedzy RSS\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Feedzy RSS</a> is a popular WordPress autoblogging plugin. It allows you to display content from unlimited RSS feeds on your website. Feedzy RSS integrates with WordAI and SpinnerCheif to rephrase the articles that you imported, so you can always add fresh content to your blog automatically.</p>\n<p>It supports complex media, including audio playback and YouTube videos. You can also blacklist keywords to fully control what you want to show on your WordPress blog.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-rss-aggregator/\" title=\"WP RSS Aggregator\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">2. WP RSS Aggregator</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-rss-aggregator/\" title=\"WP RSS Aggregator\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprssaggregator.jpg\" alt=\"WP RSS Aggregator\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236481\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprssaggregator.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprssaggregator-300x97.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprssaggregator-768x248.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-rss-aggregator/\" title=\"WP RSS Aggregator\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">WP RSS Aggregator</a> is a free and popular WordPress autoblogging plugin. It gives you the option to import, merge, and display RSS feeds from multiple resources. It also imports Atom feeds and shows them on your WordPress blog. WP RSS Aggregator has custom templates with styling options for the feeds.</p>\n<p>It supports shortcodes and blocks to display feeds on posts, pages, and custom post types. It allows you to import content from unlimited websites and even manage all sources from your WordPress dashboard&#8230;</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpematico/\" title=\"RSS Feed Fetcher\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">3. RSS Feed Fetcher</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpematico/\" title=\"RSS Feed Fetcher\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rss-feed-catcher.jpg\" alt=\"RSS Feed Catcher\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236485\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rss-feed-catcher.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rss-feed-catcher-300x97.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rss-feed-catcher-768x248.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpematico/\" title=\"RSS Feed Fetcher\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSS Feed Catcher</a> is an easy to use WordPress autoblogging plugin. It comes with an easy-to-use interface that lets you manage content that you import from other websites. You can curate content into categories and schedule them based on your preferred interval.</p>\n<p>It also imports images with the RSS feeds using WordPress functions. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cybersyn/\" title=\"CyberSEO\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">4. CyberSEO</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cybersyn/\" title=\"CyberSEO\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/cyberseo.jpg\" alt=\"CyberSEO\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236488\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/cyberseo.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/cyberseo-300x97.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/cyberseo-768x248.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cybersyn/\" title=\"CyberSEO\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">CyberSEO</a> is an advanced WordPress autoblogging and content curation plugin. It imports RSS and Atom feeds to display articles on your blog. It translates content from over 100 languages using Google Translate and Yandex Translate to publish in your language.</p>\n<p>With third-party spinners, it lets you rephrase sourced content to make sure your content isn&#8217;t plagiarized. It also embeds media content, including images and videos.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wprobot.net/\" title=\"WP Robot\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">5. WP Robot</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wprobot.net/\" title=\"WP Robot\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprobot.jpg\" alt=\"WP Robot\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236486\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprobot.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprobot-300x97.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wprobot-768x248.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wprobot.net/\" title=\"WP Robot\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">WP Robot</a> is a premium WordPress autoblogging plugin. It aggregates RSS feeds from relevant resources and publishes regular content on your blog. It allows you to customize sourced articles and works well with all <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-themes/\" title=\"The Best and Most Popular WordPress Themes (UPDATED)\">top WordPress themes</a>.</p>\n<p>It supports 30 content sources, including Amazon, eBay, YouTube, Vimeo, Flickr, etc. to import the content. You can also curate eCommerce products and sell them on your online store. It has tools for translations, content rephrasing, and more. WP Robot drip-feed the content on your blog, and even lets you publish bulk articles with 1-click manually.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-pipes/\" title=\"WP Pipes\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">6. WP Pipes</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-pipes/\" title=\"WP Pipes\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wppipes.jpg\" alt=\"WP Pipes\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236483\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wppipes.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wppipes-300x97.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/wppipes-768x248.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-pipes/\" title=\"WP Pipes\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">WP Pipes</a> is a powerful and free WordPress autoblogging plugin. It&#8217;s perfect for importing news from multiple resources and RSS feeds, and even imports WooCommerce products.</p>\n<p>WP Pipes allows you to build a pipeline of content to post on the blog. It publishes articles and WooCommerce products to your social pages like Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest, and more automatically.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rss-import/\" title=\"RSSImport\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">7. RSSImport</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rss-import/\" title=\"RSSImport\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rssimport.png\" alt=\"RSSImport\" width=\"775\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236484\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rssimport.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rssimport-300x97.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rssimport-768x248.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rss-import/\" title=\"RSSImport\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">RSSImport</a> is a simple WordPress autoblogging plugin that imports RSS feeds and display content on your blog. It supports widgets and shortcodes to post articles.</p>\n<p>You can also use template codes to add articles to your pages.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s all.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you find the best WordPress autoblogging plugin to autopilot your blog. You may also want to check out our article on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-plugins-for-user-generated-content/\" title=\"9 Best WordPress Plugins for User Generated Content\">best WordPress plugins for user generated content</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-autoblogging-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress Autoblogging Plugins to Autopilot Your Blog</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-autoblogging-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"How to A/B Split Test Your WordPress Forms to Boost Your Conversions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"https://www.isitwp.com/ab-split-test-wordpess-forms/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"https://www.isitwp.com/ab-split-test-wordpess-forms/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 23 Aug 2019 14:04:04 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"a/b test web forms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"a/b testing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"how to a/b test web forms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"split test web forms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=235515\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:614:\"<p>Do you want to A/B split test your WordPress forms? A/B split testing helps you compare two versions of your WordPress forms and determine which one performs better. There are many tools that allow you to A/B test your web forms. We use and recommend Google Optimize, the free a/b testing and personalization tool by [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/ab-split-test-wordpess-forms/\">How to A/B Split Test Your WordPress Forms to Boost Your Conversions</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16400:\"<p>Do you want to A/B split test your WordPress forms? A/B split testing helps you compare two versions of your WordPress forms and determine which one performs better. </p>\n<p>There are many tools that allow you to A/B test your web forms. We use and recommend Google Optimize, the free a/b testing and personalization tool by Google. </p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to A/B split test your WordPress forms to boost your conversions.</p>\n<h3>Why Should You A/B Split Test WordPress Forms?</h3>\n<p>Your web form is the first point where an actual interaction with your customer begins. Not to mention, it should be impactful so as to encourage more people to fill in the details.  </p>\n<p>A/B split testing allows you to create one or more variants of any web form. </p>\n<p>For example, in your variant, you can add an additional form field, change the placeholder, change the copy of the button or anything else that you can think of that would bring in more engagement. Once you created a variant, by default, half of your traffic is shown the original version of the page and half are shown the modified version.</p>\n<p>After the test, you&#8217;ll get to know which form is driving more conversions, so you can stick to the one that resonates best with your audience.</p>\n<h3>Choosing the Right A/B Testing Tool for WordPress &#8211; Google Optimize</h3>\n<p>We use and recommend Google Optimize to set up a/b tests. Google Optimize is a free A/B testing and personalization solution by Google. Best of all, it&#8217;s natively integrated with Google Analytics so you can use your Analytics data to create experiments quickly and easily.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\" title=\"MonsterInsights\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">MonsterInsights</a> is the best plugin that lets you easily connect Google Analytics and Google Optimize on your WordPress website. With MonsterInsights, you don&#8217;t have to touch a single line of code to set up Google Optimize. All you have to do is to install the Google Optimize addon and you&#8217;ll be ready to start experiments. </p>\n<h4>Step 1: Get Started With Google Optimize</h4>\n<p>The first thing you&#8217;ll need to do is to install and activate the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\" title=\"MonsterInsights\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">MonsterInsights</a> plugin. For more details, check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-google-analytics-wordpress-site/\" title=\"How to Install Google Analytics\">how to connect Google Analytics with MonsterInsights.</a></p>\n<p>Once you completed the set up process, you need to visit <strong>Insights &raquo; Addons</strong> and install the <strong>Google Optimize</strong> Addon.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/googleoptimizeaddon.jpg\" alt=\"Google Optimize Addon\" width=\"775\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236108\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/googleoptimizeaddon.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/googleoptimizeaddon-300x77.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/googleoptimizeaddon-768x198.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you need to create an account on <a href=\"https://www.google.com/analytics/optimize/\" title=\"Google Optimize\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Google Optimize</a>.</p>\n<p>Once logged in, hit the <strong>Get Started</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/get-started.jpg\" alt=\"Get started\" width=\"775\" height=\"358\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236105\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/get-started.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/get-started-300x139.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/get-started-768x355.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll be asked to agree to the terms and conditions. Finally, click on the <strong>Finished</strong> button, and you&#8217;ll be directed to the main page.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/finised-setting.jpg\" alt=\"Finished and redirected\" width=\"775\" height=\"328\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236106\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/finised-setting.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/finised-setting-300x127.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/finised-setting-768x325.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you&#8217;ll see a container information section on the right-hand side of the screen. </p>\n<p>Google automatically creates an Account ID and Container ID for you. However, you have the option to change them if you want by clicking on Edit Container Details.</p>\n<p>The account section allows you to run your A/B testing experiments and the container is where your Optimize configurations for your A/B testing experiments are saved. You can click on the three vertical dots to edit container details and manage notifications.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-container.jpg\" alt=\"Edit container\" width=\"775\" height=\"336\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236109\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-container.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-container-300x130.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-container-768x333.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>The container information is created by Google automatically. However, you can change the container name, account ID, and container ID in this section.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Link Google Optimize to Your Google Analytics Account</h3>\n<p>In order to start collecting your A/B testing data on Google Analytics, you&#8217;ll need to link your Google Optimize to Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>To link the accounts, On the right-hand side of your screen, you need to expand the <strong>Link to Google Analytics</strong> section and click on the <strong>Link Property</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-property.jpg\" alt=\"Link property\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236110\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-property.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-property-300x135.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-property-768x347.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now click on the dropdown to select a property that you want to link with Google Optimize. If you don&#8217;t find the property that you want to link, then follow this guide to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-a-property-in-google-analytics/\" title=\"How to Create a Property in Google Analytics\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">create a property in Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-analytics.jpg\" alt=\"Link analytics\" width=\"775\" height=\"360\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236136\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-analytics.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-analytics-300x139.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/link-analytics-768x357.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Data can now flow between both your Google Optimize and Analytics accounts.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Add Google Optimize to WordPress</h3>\n<p>MonsterInsights makes it easy for you to add Google Optimize to your website using the <strong>Optimize</strong> addon that you&#8217;ve installed previously.</p>\n<p>To do this, you&#8217;ll need the container ID which is available in the container information section. Copy the container ID from there.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/container-id.jpg\" alt=\"Container ID\" width=\"776\" height=\"183\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236112\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/container-id.jpg 776w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/container-id-300x71.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/container-id-768x181.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 776px) 100vw, 776px\" /></p>\n<p>Now head over to your WordPress admin area and visit <strong>Insights &raquo; Settings &raquo; Tracking &raquo; Google Optimize</strong> to paste the Google Optimize Container ID.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mi-container-id.jpg\" alt=\"Container ID\" width=\"775\" height=\"375\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236113\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mi-container-id.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mi-container-id-300x145.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mi-container-id-768x372.jpg 768w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mi-container-id-330x160.jpg 330w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Click on the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. You have successfully added Google Optimize to your website.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Start the A/B Test Experiment</h3>\n<p>Now you can start A/B split testing for your WordPress forms. For the sake of this tutorial, we&#8217;ll take a signup form as an example to run the test.</p>\n<p>You need to visit your Google Optimize account and click on the <strong>Let&#8217;s Go</strong> button to create an experiment.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/create-experiment.jpg\" alt=\"Create an experiment\" width=\"775\" height=\"385\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236120\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/create-experiment.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/create-experiment-300x149.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/create-experiment-768x382.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>A sidebar popup will appear where you&#8217;ll be asked to enter the name of your experiment and URL of the signup form page.</p>\n<p>After specifying the details, you&#8217;ll need to select the type of experiment/test you want to perform on your specified URL.</p>\n<p>Click on the <strong>A/B Test</strong> option which allows you to test two or more variants of a page.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ab-test-experiment.jpg\" alt=\"A/B Test\" width=\"775\" height=\"294\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236126\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ab-test-experiment.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ab-test-experiment-300x114.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/ab-test-experiment-768x291.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Once selected, click on the <strong>Create</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Now you&#8217;ll notice that your test is still in the <strong>Draft</strong> mode. To start the experiment, you&#8217;ll need to take a few more steps. Start by adding a variant to your original signup form. To do that, click on the <strong>Add Variant</strong> button and type a name for the variant you want to create.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-variant.jpg\" alt=\"Add variant\" width=\"775\" height=\"319\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236127\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-variant.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-variant-300x123.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/add-variant-768x316.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now click on the <strong>Edit</strong> button to make changes in the new variant of your signup form.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant.jpg\" alt=\"Edit variant\" width=\"775\" height=\"167\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236128\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant-300x65.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant-768x165.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>This will take you to the <strong>Optimize Visual Editor</strong> where you can customize the size of the fields, change labels, edit button text, and more.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optimizeeditor.jpg\" alt=\"Optimize Visual Editor\" width=\"775\" height=\"355\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236129\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optimizeeditor.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optimizeeditor-300x137.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optimizeeditor-768x352.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you make all the changes, click on the <strong>Save</strong> and <strong>Finished</strong> buttons.</p>\n<p>After that, you need to define the objectives for your A/B test. These objectives will help you decide which signup form variant the winner is.</p>\n<p>Click on the <strong>Add Experiment Objective</strong> link. There are many pre-defined objectives, including pageviews, bounces, and session durations. You can also set a custom objective for the experiment.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounces.jpg\" alt=\"Bounces\" width=\"775\" height=\"195\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236130\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounces.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounces-300x75.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/bounces-768x193.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>For this experiment, we&#8217;ll be choosing <strong>Bounces</strong> as our objective to find out which signup form has the lowest bounce rate.</p>\n<p>You can also custom objectives that are not mentioned in the account.</p>\n<p>Finally, you&#8217;ll need to define a percentage for how many people should see the original sign up form and its variant.</p>\n<p>By default, if you only have one variant, the traffic will be split equally between the original page and its variant.</p>\n<p>You can click on the weight to customize it, but make sure the balance weight is 100%.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant-weight.jpg\" alt=\"Edit variant weight\" width=\"775\" height=\"440\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236132\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant-weight.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant-weight-300x170.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/edit-variant-weight-768x436.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, click on the <strong>Finished</strong> button.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s all. You can click on the <strong>Start</strong> button to start your experiment.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/start-experiment.jpg\" alt=\"Start experiment\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236133\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/start-experiment.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/start-experiment-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/start-experiment-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s advised to at least run the A/B test experiment for two weeks or more to make sure you&#8217;ve gathered enough data. Once enough data has been collected, Google will declare a winner.</p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you learn how to A/B test WordPress forms. You may also want to check out the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-analytics-solutions-compared/\" title=\"13 Best WordPress Analytics Plugins\">best WordPress analytics plugins</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/ab-split-test-wordpess-forms/\">How to A/B Split Test Your WordPress Forms to Boost Your Conversions</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://www.isitwp.com/ab-split-test-wordpess-forms/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\